00:00:29.585 --> 00:00:31.545
who they really are.

00:01:35.305 --> 00:01:38.785
1 MONTH BEFORE THE ELECTION

00:01:41.785 --> 00:01:43.905
Has anyone ever wondered, like I have,

00:01:44.665 --> 00:01:45.665
why…

00:01:46.185 --> 00:01:48.265
whenever we talk about change,

00:01:48.905 --> 00:01:53.505
adults always say that change takes time?

00:01:54.825 --> 00:01:55.865
How many years?

00:01:55.945 --> 00:01:57.025
Three years?

00:01:57.545 --> 00:01:58.585
Five years?

00:01:58.665 --> 00:02:02.425
Sometimes, I'm no longer sure

00:02:02.985 --> 00:02:04.745
whether it's a real reason

00:02:05.305 --> 00:02:07.505
or just an excuse to do nothing at all.

00:02:09.665 --> 00:02:10.705
Yes!

00:02:10.785 --> 00:02:11.825
-You're right.
-Yes!

00:02:11.905 --> 00:02:15.025
I'm not saying that change is easy.

00:02:16.265 --> 00:02:17.745
But my point is

00:02:18.665 --> 00:02:20.705
that if we start
by doing just one thing at a time,

00:02:21.665 --> 00:02:24.345
we'll only see one result at a time.

00:02:26.305 --> 00:02:28.865
But if we start
by doing 100 things at once,

00:02:30.785 --> 00:02:33.145
the progress of 100 years

00:02:33.665 --> 00:02:36.225
might happen within a single year.

00:02:36.745 --> 00:02:37.585
Right?

00:02:37.665 --> 00:02:38.665
Right!

00:02:45.305 --> 00:02:49.545
Paradorn.

00:02:49.625 --> 00:02:54.225
Paradorn.

00:03:05.265 --> 00:03:06.825
Hello.

00:03:06.905 --> 00:03:08.505
I'm Nanno, Number 2,

00:03:11.225 --> 00:03:13.345
here with a policy…

00:03:16.705 --> 00:03:18.705
What policy should I go with?

00:03:20.465 --> 00:03:21.385
Oh.

00:03:21.905 --> 00:03:24.145
"New student, new life," then.

00:03:25.145 --> 00:03:28.665
Anyway, please take care of me,

00:03:29.705 --> 00:03:31.665
and my heart too.

00:03:35.385 --> 00:03:37.385
I just applied recently,

00:03:37.905 --> 00:03:40.225
so I didn't really prepare any policies.

00:03:40.305 --> 00:03:42.065
But that's okay, right?

00:03:42.585 --> 00:03:44.345
I'd rather hear ideas from everyone.

00:03:52.145 --> 00:03:55.105
Did she copy our idea?
She just changed the wording.

00:03:55.185 --> 00:03:57.545
I'm ready to kiss everyone now.

00:04:17.385 --> 00:04:18.345
Hey!

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:20.505
-Me first!
-Me first!

00:04:20.585 --> 00:04:22.025
Hurry up.

00:04:22.105 --> 00:04:24.505
Go, go. Hurry.

00:04:24.585 --> 00:04:26.705
The line is long now.

00:04:28.225 --> 00:04:30.425
Wow.

00:04:49.345 --> 00:04:51.985
I'm Nanno, No. 2. Please support me.

00:04:52.705 --> 00:04:53.545
Sure.

00:05:02.825 --> 00:05:04.865
I really like your idea.

00:05:10.345 --> 00:05:12.065
So I'd like to…

00:05:17.945 --> 00:05:19.425
